<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8"/>
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"/>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
    <title>Awesome Elixir - list of libraries</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="<%= Routes.static_path(@conn, "/css/app.css") %>"/>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="container app_header">
        <h1>Awesome Elixir</h1>
        <nav>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <a href="/">All</a>
            </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/?min_stars=10">&ge;10⭐</a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/?min_stars=50">&ge;50⭐</a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/?min_stars=100">&ge;100⭐</a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/?min_stars=500">&ge;500⭐</a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="/?min_stars=1000">&ge;1000⭐</a>
              </li>
          </ul>
        </nav>
        <p>
          Elixir is awesome. And it has a vast awesome list: <a href="https://github.com/h4cc/awesome-elixir" target="_blank">h4cc/awesome-elixir</a>.
          This is a mirror of it where each library is marked with number of
          stars at Github and number of days since
          the last commit.
        </p>
    </header>

    <main role="main" class="container">
      <p class="alert alert-info" role="alert"><%= get_flash(@conn, :info) %></p>
      <p class="alert alert-danger" role="alert"><%= get_flash(@conn, :error) %></p>
      <%= render @view_module, @view_template, assigns %>
    </main>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="<%= Routes.static_path(@conn, "/js/app.js") %>"></script>
  </body>
</html>
